The tax falls squarely on London and the South East, with three quarters of potentially taxable homes located in these two regions. There are many retired professionals living modestly in homes they bought in the 1970s and 1980s. If these once-affordable homes are redesignated as “mansions” and taxed accordingly, their owners would have to sell.
